    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ITALIAN DESSERTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen DeMasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bindi Dessert Services Inc, importer and distributor of Italian desserts, purchases 30,000-square-foot abandoned chemical company building in Belleville, NJ, and will open its first manufacturing plant in US (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bindi Dessert Services Inc., an importer and distributor of Italian desserts, has purchased a 30,000-square-foot abandoned chemical company building in Belleville and will open its first manufacturing plant in the United States. The Totowa-based company now imports its desserts from Italy. Remodeling the building will start next month and production should start by next summer. Gelato, an Italian ice, and Sorbetto, fruit-based sorbet, will be manufactured at the plant. Cakes and tarts will continue to be imported from Italy.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
